\pard\f0\fs28 Dwarf shrubs. Leaves simple, alternate; margins entire, erose or remotely toothed. Capitula usually solitary at the ends of branches. Involucral bracts imbricate, in up to 5 rows. Receptacle flat; scales absent. Florets yellowish, all tubular, the outer female, the inner hermaphrodite. Achenes cylindrical, somewhat compressed or angled, unbeaked, usually hairy. Pappus-hairs in 1-2 rows, simple, free.
\par 
