\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. sordidum} (L.) Reichenb., {\i Fl. Germ. Excurs.} 224 (1831). Dwarf shrub up to 30 cm. Stems lanate, densely leafy. Leaves 1-3 cm, linear, densely lanate on both surfaces, entire; margin strongly revolute. Flowering stems with 2-6 small, sessile to shortly pedunculate, clustered capitula. Involucral bracts ovate, acute, brownish, all more or less similar, denticulate.{\i  Rocks and walls. S.W. Europe, extending eastwards to C. Italy.} Bl Co Ga Hs It Sa.
