\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. L. leyseroides} (Desf.) Maire, {\i Bull. Soc. Hist. Nat. Afr. Nord}{\b  20}: 186 (1929). Stems 5-15 cm, branched, glandular-pubescent. Leaves linear, glandular-pubescent. Peduncles c. 4 cm, slender, axillary, erecto-patent, becoming erect just below the capitulum. Involucre 8-9 mm, glabrous; bracts mostly scarious, obtuse. Ligules c. 1 mm.{\i  Dry, sandy places. S.E. Spain} ({\i near Almeria}). Hs. ({\i North Africa.})
