\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial, rarely biennial herbs or small shrubs. Leaves simple, alternate. Capitula solitary or in a corymbose or paniculate inflorescence. Involucral bracts imbricate, in many rows. Receptacle flat or slightly convex, without scales. Florets yellow, the outer ligulate, female, the ligule often very short. Tubular florets hermaphrodite. Achenes angled, not abruptly contracted below the pappus. Pappus-hairs simple, free.
